title: 820-3330 power cycling on magsafe
message: Ok so I have a liquid damaged 820-3330 it’s been worked on previously as I found out further into working on it. It starts with a charged battery but with a charger will get green light but power cycling with fan spin and green light going off then coming back on and fan spin/green light. I’ve tried replacing Q7030, Q7035, Q7055 and U7000 and have checked R7021 & R7022 at c7020 and get 20 ohms, R7051 and R7052 are also correct. Anyone have any ideas?

message:

If not, check with fake charger, or lab PSU.

title: 820-3330 power cycling on magsafe
message:
Be aware this board requires 85W charger to start without battery.
However it should work with battery and even 45W charger connected.
A bad DCIN board can block battery charging.
SMC will not charge the battery, if cannot communicate properly with 1-wire memory from Magsafe cable.
